12 their cash surrender values, in the aggregate from all life insurance
13 companies shall not at any time exceed thirty-five percent of the paid-up
14 capital, surplus, undivided profits, and capital notes and debentures of
15 such bank. The limitations under this subsection on a bank's purchase of
16 life insurance contracts, in the aggregate from all life insurance
17 companies, shall not apply to any contract purchased prior to April 5,
18 1994.
